OL,0,        ECIMSBWebfax     F398A1747315525
OL,3,CDad forced to carry disabled son up
OL,4,Cstairs after seven-month wait for home
OL,6,F"They're frozen in time because
OL,7,Fthere's so much they should be getting
OL,8,Fbut they're not. There's no light at
OL,9,Fthe end of the tunnel, it's just
OL,10,Fgetting dimmer and dimmer."
OL,12,FStephen's son Harry believes the
OL,13,Fcondition of their living space is
OL,14,Fmaking his son's health worse.
OL,16,FMost people with cerebral palsy have
OL,17,Fmobility issues, but regular exercise
OL,18,Fand play are crucial for maintaining
OL,19,Fand improving their physical strength.
OL,1,W~k4j5 hw1~k4~c1 hw}h7}j7}      G4/9
