OL,3,CDad forced to carry disabled son up
OL,4,Cstairs after seven-month wait for home
OL,6,FStephen said: "The physio said it's
OL,7,Fgetting worse and it could get to a
OL,8,Fpoint where he won't be able to
OL,9,Fstretch his legs out.
OL,11,F"He gets in the bath, but he's
OL,12,Fbruising his legs. With a wet room
OL,13,Fhe'd be in his wheelchair and have a
OL,14,Fproper shower. It'd be so much easier."
OL,16,FThe pain from his legs can cause Harry
OL,17,Fto cry out in pain, much to the
OL,18,Fdistress of his brothers.
OL,1,W~k4j5 hw1~k4~c1 hw}h7}j7}      G5/9
