OL,3,CDad forced to carry disabled son up
OL,4,Cstairs after seven-month wait for home
OL,6,FHe worries that even when he does find
OL,7,Fa new home, his housing association
OL,8,FHalton Housing will not pay for the
OL,9,Fadaptations needed to help Harry.
OL,11,FIn response, Halton Housing said:
OL,12,F"Since being made aware of Mr Murray's
OL,13,Fchange of circumstances, we've been
OL,14,Fworking closely with him to support a
OL,15,Fmove to a more suitable home that will
OL,16,Fmeet his family's needs."
OL,1,W~k4j5 hw1~k4~c1 hw}h7}j7}      G7/9
