OL,0,        ECIMSBWebfax     F398A1747315525
OL,3,CDad forced to carry disabled son up
OL,4,Cstairs after seven-month wait for home
OL,6,F"Halton Housing have been informed
OL,7,Fthat I am very unhappy with their
OL,8,Fresponse, I have asked for further
OL,9,Fassistance for Mr Murray and his
OL,10,Fchildren."
OL,12,FUntil a suitable home is found,
OL,13,FStephen will have to continue carrying
OL,14,Fhis son up a narrow hallway at least
OL,15,Ftwice a day.
OL,17,FHe said: "People have said 'what would
OL,18,Fhappen if you hurt your back? Well I'd
OL,19,Fbe knackered wouldn't I? What am I
OL,20,Fmeant to do? I've got to carry him
OL,21,Fupstairs or we sleep in my car."
OL,1,W~k4j5 hw1~k4~c1 hw}h7}j7}      G9/9
